g process:Intro Call (20 min) get to know you, your experience, and your motivationTechnical Pairing (1 hr) collaborative coding session over video callPaid Trial Day work with the team on a real engineering challenge (remote or onsite)Final Debrief & OfferWe value transparency and fast feedback at every step.RequirementsYou are an experienced engineer who loves building robust, elegant systems that serve real product needs.You have:5+ years' experience as a product-focused software engineerExperience writing well-tested, maintainable code in a statically-typed language (TypeScript, Go, Rust, Java/Scala...)Strong fundamentals in API design, database modeling, scalability, and system performanceExperience deploying and maintaining systems on AWS, using tools such as Terraform, Docker, and KubernetesThe ability to work across the stack when needed but with a clear backend focus (data, APIs, infra)Excellent communication skills: you can explain complex technical concepts with clarityBonus points for:Experience building high-performance canvas or visualization interfaces (D3, Observable Plot)Exposure to PyTorch or machine-learning pipelinesKnowledge of on-prem or hybrid cloud deploymentsMindset and values:We're looking for someone who:Is product-oriented: you care about impact, not just elegant codeIs scientifically curious and thrives on complex, technical challengesWorks with low ego and collaborates transparentlyEnjoys autonomy but knows when to ask questions and seek alignmentHas a long-term mindset: ready to help build a company, not just a productCommunicates openly and values shared learningTeam and culture:You'll join a small, tight-knit group of engineers and scientists who are building Polaron's product and culture together. We operate with:High trust and ownershipPragmatism over dogmaCuriosity, humility, and scientific disciplineA strong focus on quality, impact, and long-term maintainabilityWhat we value at Polaron:STEM mindset: genuine curiosity for science and the physical worldHunger to learn: proactive, self-driven, and impact-orientedPragmatism: you prefer solutions that work over theoretical perfectionLow ego & empathy: you lift others up, you listen, you share knowledgeLong-term commitment: you want to grow with the company and shape its journeyBenefitsSalary: \u00a3100,000 - \u00a3140,000 depending on experienceEquity: meaningful stock options in a growing companyHolidays: 25 days + 2 \"festive leave\" daysPerks: gym membership, free barista coffeeLocation: Shoreditch Exchange (Hoxton, London)\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "London, England, United Kingdom", "loc": "IN_LONDON", "arr_raw": "Based in East London", "arr": "IN_OFFICE", "sen_raw": "Senior", "sen": "LEVEL_3", "tech_raw": "TypeScript, React, Next.js, Express, Prisma, Python (PyTorch), PostgreSQL, Docker, Kubernetes, AWS, Terraform", "tech": ["REACT", "JS_TS", "AI_ML"], "comp_raw": "\u00a3100,000 - \u00a3140,000 depending on experience", "comp": "ABOVE_100K"}}
