{"index": 89, "title": "Marketing Manager, Integrated Campaigns & Events, tvScientific", "job_location": "Description: About PinterestMillions of people around the world come to our platform to find creative ideas, dream about new possibilities and plan for memories that will last a lifetime. At Pinterest, we\u2019re on a mission to bring everyone the inspiration to create a life they love, and that starts with the people behind the product.Discover a career where you ignite innovation for millions, transform passion into growth opportunities, celebrate each other\u2019s unique experiences and embrace the flexibility to do your best work. Creating a career you love? It\u2019s Possible.About TvScientifictvScientific is the first and only CTV advertising platform purpose-built for performance marketers. We leverage massive data and cutting-edge science to automate and optimize TV advertising to drive business outcomes. Our solution combines media buying, optimization, measurement, and attribution in one, efficient platform. Our platform is built by industry leaders with a long history in programmatic advertising, digital media, and ad verification who have now purpose-built a CTV performance platform advertisers can trust to grow their business.tvScientific is looking for a Marketing Manager to help position tvScientific as a leader in CTV advertising. In this role, you\u2019ll lead the planning and execution of high-priority corporate marketing initiatives \u2014 including Tier 1 campaigns and key industry events \u2014 ensuring they run smoothly, stay on track, and deliver maximum impact. This is a hands-on role for a strategic, highly organized marketer who thrives in fast-moving environments, brings clarity and structure to complex cross-functional projects, and has a proven track record of successfully managing integrated marketing campaigns and event logistics.What You'll Do Campaign Strategy & Planning: Own the planning process for our Tier 1 integrated marketing campaigns. Partner with marketing leadership to define campaign goals, audiences, key messages, success metrics, and integrated launch plans.Campaign Project Management: Build and manage campaign timelines, deliverables, dependencies, and stakeholder ownership. Lead kickoffs and weekly status check-ins, and ensure campaigns ship on time and with high quality.Event Planning: Own planning and logistics for key industry events and hosted activations, including conferences, partner events, ancillary events, etc. Manage vendor relationships, run of show, internal communications, and on-site readiness.Campaign & Event Operations: Create repeatable systems, templates, and processes to improve how we run campaigns and events. Maintain campaign calendars, checklists, and launch playbooks that bring clarity and consistency to execution.Cross-Functional Coordination: Act as the quarterback for campaign execution across teams (content, design, product marketing, growth marketing, sales, leadership, etc.). Ensure stakeholders have clear expectations, deadlines, and accountability.Performance Tracking & Reporting: Partner with growth marketing and marketing leadership to ensure campaign and event results are tracked and reported. Support post-mortems and continuous improvement by documenting learnings and recommending improvements.How We'll Define SuccessCreating high-quality campaigns that are launched on time, with clear ownership.Planning events that run smoothly and professionally, and contribute to increased brand awareness and opportunity generation.Building a stronger operational rhythm for both events and campaigns, including defined timelines, templates, and planning cadences.Increasing leadership visibility into upcoming campaign launches and event priorities.What We\u2019re Looking For 5+ years of experience in events and/or integrated marketing, ideally in B2B tech or ad tech.Bachelor\u2019s degree in a relevant field such as Marketing, a related field, or equivalent experience.Strong examples of running cross-functional projects with many stakeholders and deadlines.Experience planning and executing long-running marketing campaigns.Experience managing event logistics and operations.Exceptional communication and stakeholder management skills.Highly organized, detailed-oriented, and reliable under deadlines.Comfortable in a fast-paced, startup environment, with the ability to adapt to changing priorities.Nice-to-haves:Experience in ad tech, marketing tech, or performance marketingFamiliarity with TV advertising, CTV/OTT, or the media landscapePrevious experience in a startup environmentExperience using AsanaIn-Office Requirement StatementWe recognize that the ideal environment for work is situational and may differ across departments. What this looks like day-to-day can vary based on the needs of each organization or role.This role will need to be in the office for in-person collaboration a few times per year, and therefore can be situated anywhere in the country.Expect regular travel for this particular role.Relocation Statement:This position is not eligible for relocation assistance. Visit our PinFlex page to learn more about our working model.At Pinterest we believe the workplace should be equitable, inclusive, and inspiring for every employee. In an effort to provide greater transparency, we are sharing the base salary range for this position. The position is also eligible for equity. Final salary is based on a number of factors including location, travel, relevant prior experience, or particular skills and expertise.Information regarding the culture at Pinterest and benefits available for this position can be found here.US based applicants only$98,561\u2014$202,918 USDOur Commitment To InclusionPinterest is an equal opportunity employer and makes employment decisions on the basis of merit. We want to have the best qualified people in every job. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without rega